---
// LanguageGroundingFigure — concept illustration for the homepage About section.
// The main line, in one picture: one meaning is realized in three different
// linguistic surfaces (German morphology, English word order, Chinese context),
// and the question is what carries the model's answer — the meaning (structure →
// grounded, so it stays stable as the form changes) or the surface (spurious →
// it breaks when the form changes).
// Visual language continues the rest of the site:
//   amber  = the meaning / genuine structure / grounded
//   coral  = surface / spurious (x'd, as in the SC figure)
//   deep-purple = language / linguistic form (the typological accent)
---

<figure class="lg-fig" aria-label="One meaning realized in three linguistic surfaces — German morphology, English word order, Chinese context — and the question of what carries the model's answer: the meaning (grounded, stable as the form changes) or the surface (spurious, breaks when the form changes).">
  <svg viewBox="0 0 400 360" width="400" height="360" preserveAspectRatio="xMidYMid meet">
    <!-- ONE MEANING (the language-independent content) -->
    <text class="lg-tag lg-tag-amber" x="200" y="26" text-anchor="middle">ONE MEANING</text>
    <circle class="lg-halo" cx="200" cy="64" r="21" />
    <circle class="lg-meaning" cx="200" cy="64" r="11" />

    <!-- fan: the one meaning, carried by three different surfaces (ends just above each form) -->
    <line class="lg-fan" x1="200" y1="77" x2="82" y2="138" />
    <line class="lg-fan" x1="200" y1="77" x2="200" y2="138" />
    <line class="lg-fan" x1="200" y1="77" x2="318" y2="138" />

    <!-- DE — morphology (a suffix on the stem carries it) -->
    <rect class="lg-form" x="52" y="146" width="56" height="20" rx="10" />
    <line class="lg-form-div" x1="88" y1="146" x2="88" y2="166" />
    <rect class="lg-form-fill" x="89" y="147.5" width="17" height="17" rx="7" />
    <text class="lg-word" x="80" y="192" text-anchor="middle"><tspan class="lg-langp">DE</tspan> · morphology</text>

    <!-- EN — word order (a slot/position carries it) -->
    <rect class="lg-form" x="172" y="146" width="14" height="18" rx="2" />
    <rect class="lg-form-fill" x="193" y="146" width="14" height="18" rx="2" />
    <rect class="lg-form" x="214" y="146" width="14" height="18" rx="2" />
    <text class="lg-word" x="200" y="192" text-anchor="middle"><tspan class="lg-langp">EN</tspan> · word order</text>

    <!-- ZH — context (the surrounding context carries it) -->
    <rect class="lg-form" x="312" y="146" width="16" height="18" rx="2" />
    <ellipse class="lg-ring" cx="320" cy="155" rx="28" ry="18" />
    <text class="lg-word" x="320" y="192" text-anchor="middle"><tspan class="lg-langp">ZH</tspan> · context</text>

    <!-- divider + the grounding question -->
    <line class="lg-rule" x1="64" y1="224" x2="336" y2="224" />
    <text class="lg-q" x="200" y="252" text-anchor="middle">what carries the model's answer?</text>

    <!-- two tidy outcomes -->
    <circle class="lg-dot-grounded" cx="72" cy="288" r="6" />
    <text class="lg-out" x="88" y="292">
      <tspan class="lg-out-amber">the meaning</tspan><tspan class="lg-out-dim"> — grounded, stable across forms</tspan>
    </text>

    <circle class="lg-dot-spurious" cx="72" cy="322" r="6" />
    <g class="lg-x" transform="translate(72,322)">
      <line x1="-3.4" y1="-3.4" x2="3.4" y2="3.4" />
      <line x1="3.4" y1="-3.4" x2="-3.4" y2="3.4" />
    </g>
    <text class="lg-out" x="88" y="326">
      <tspan class="lg-out-coral">the surface</tspan><tspan class="lg-out-dim"> — spurious, breaks across forms</tspan>
    </text>
  </svg>
</figure>

<style>
  .lg-fig { margin: 0; padding: 0; }
  .lg-fig svg { width: 100%; max-width: 440px; height: auto; display: block; margin: 0 auto; }

  .lg-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    fill: var(--color-text-muted);
  }
  .lg-tag-amber { fill: var(--accent-amber); }

  .lg-halo { fill: var(--accent-amber); opacity: 0.14; }
  .lg-meaning { fill: var(--accent-amber); }

  .lg-fan { stroke: var(--color-border-strong); stroke-width: 1; }

  .lg-form { fill: none; stroke: var(--accent-deep-purple); stroke-width: 1.2; stroke-opacity: 0.75; }
  .lg-form-div { stroke: var(--accent-deep-purple); stroke-width: 1; stroke-opacity: 0.55; }
  .lg-form-fill { fill: var(--accent-deep-purple); opacity: 0.8; }
  .lg-ring {
    fill: none;
    stroke: var(--accent-deep-purple);
    stroke-width: 1;
    stroke-opacity: 0.6;
    stroke-dasharray: 3 3;
  }
  .lg-word {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 9.5px;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    fill: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
  }
  .lg-langp {
    fill: var(--accent-deep-purple);
    font-style: normal;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
  }

  .lg-rule { stroke: var(--color-border-strong); stroke-width: 1; stroke-opacity: 0.6; }
  .lg-q {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    fill: var(--color-text-muted);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .lg-dot-grounded { fill: var(--accent-amber); }
  .lg-dot-spurious { fill: var(--accent-coral); }
  .lg-x line { stroke: var(--color-bg); stroke-width: 1.3; stroke-linecap: round; }

  .lg-out { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 9.5px; letter-spacing: 0.01em; }
  .lg-out-amber { fill: var(--accent-amber); }
  .lg-out-coral { fill: var(--accent-coral); }
  .lg-out-dim { fill: var(--color-text-dim); }
</style>
